# Searching a msgvault archive

{{template "basics" .}}

## Find messages

```bash
msgvault search "quarterly report" --json -n 20
msgvault search from:alice@example.com has:attachment after:2024-01-01 --json
msgvault search subject:invoice larger:1M --account you@gmail.com --json
```

Positional arguments are joined into one query string, so quoting the
whole query is optional.

### Query operators (Gmail-like)

| Operator | Meaning | Value format |
|---|---|---|
| `from:` `to:` `cc:` `bcc:` | address filter | full email, or bare domain (`from:example.com`) |
| `subject:` | subject substring | text |
| `label:` (alias `l:`) | Gmail label | label name |
| `has:attachment` | has ≥1 attachment | — |
| `before:` `after:` | sent date | `YYYY-MM-DD` |
| `older_than:` `newer_than:` | relative age | `7d`, `2w`, `1m`, `1y` |
| `larger:` `smaller:` | whole-message size | `5M`, `100K`, `1G` |
| `message_type:` | source kind | `email`, `sms`, `mms`, `whatsapp`, `imessage`, `teams`, `fbmessenger`, `calendar_event`, `synctech_sms_call`, `google_voice_text`, `google_voice_call`, `google_voice_voicemail` |

Bare words and `"quoted phrases"` are full-text terms, matched as
prefixes and combined with AND (no OR/NEAR support). If a search
returns nothing, retry with fewer terms or fewer filters.

### Modes

- Default `--mode=fts`: full-text index. Supports `--offset` paging and
  filter-only queries (no free text, e.g. only `from:alice@example.com`
  with `--account`).
- `--mode=hybrid` or `--mode=vector`: semantic search. Requires a built
  embeddings index and at least one free-text term; `--offset` is not
  supported. `--explain` adds per-signal scores. If these fail with an
  embeddings error, fall back to `--mode=fts`.

### Scoping flags

- `--account <email>` or `--collection <name>` (mutually exclusive)
- `--message-type <type>` (repeatable)
- `--limit` / `-n` (default 50), `--offset` (fts only)

### Search result JSON fields

`id`, `source_message_id`, `conversation_id`, `source_conversation_id`,
`subject`, `snippet`, `from_email`, `from_name`, `sent_at` (RFC3339),
`size_estimate`, `has_attachments`, `attachment_count`, `labels`.

## Read a message

```bash
msgvault show-message 12345 --json
msgvault export-eml 12345 -o message.eml
```

`show-message --json` returns full headers, recipients, labels, an
`attachments` array, and `body_text` / `body_html`. `export-eml` writes
the raw MIME message (attachments included); `-o -` streams to stdout.

## Recipes

- Paginate: increase `--offset` by `--limit` until fewer than `--limit`
  rows come back (fts mode only).
- Count matches for a filter: prefer the msgvault-analytics skill
  (aggregates and SQL) over paging through search results.

